@page
@model OfficeManagement.Pages.PrivacyModel

@{
    Layout = null;
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"] - ASP Management</title>

    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/Privacy.css" />
</head>
<body class="bg-light">
    <main class="privacy-page py-5">
        <div class="container privacy-container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
                    <div class="privacy-card p-4">
                        <h1 class="privacy-title mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>

                        <p class="lead mb-4">
                            This Privacy Policy describes how Office Management collects, uses, and discloses personal information when you use our website and services.
                        </p>

                        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
                        <p>
                            We collect information you provide directly to us when you register an account, update your profile, communicate with us, or use features that require personal data. This may include:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Contact information (name, email, phone)</li>
                            <li>Profile details (job title, department, avatar)</li>
                            <li>Account credentials (hashed passwords)</li>
                            <li>Usage data and analytics</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                        <p>We use collected information to:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
                            <li>Authenticate and manage accounts</li>
                            <li>Communicate about updates, security alerts, and administrative messages</li>
                            <li>Analyze usage and trends to enhance user experience</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
                        <p>
                            We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to operate and improve our site. You can control cookie preferences in your browser settings. Third-party analytics providers (e.g., Google Analytics) may also use cookies to collect information about your use of the site.
                        </p>

                        <h2>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
                        <p>
                            We will not sell your personal information. We may share information with:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Service providers who perform services on our behalf</li>
                            <li>Law enforcement or regulators when required by law</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
                        <p>
                            We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect personal information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.
                        </p>

                        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
                        <p>We retain personal information for as long as necessary to provide the services, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce policies.</p>

                        <h2>7. Children</h2>
                        <p>Our services are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.</p>

                        <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
                        <p>Our site may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites.</p>

                        <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
                        <p>
                            Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete your personal data. To exercise these rights or for privacy inquiries, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@yourdomain.com">privacy@yourdomain.com</a>.
                        </p>

                        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated policy with a revised effective date.</p>

                        <div class="mt-4 d-flex justify-content-end">
                            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary me-2" href="/Index">Back to Home</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
